28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Please see the course LUNA pages for the schedule and topics for today.</span></span></div>", ""], "第15回": ["<div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">[</span></span></span><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"> Flex Hours </span></span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">]</span></span></span></div><div><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">\"Online class (Format will be announced in each class)\" /&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">《</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">360 minutes</span></span></span><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">》</span></span></span></div><div><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">Please see the course LUNA pages for the schedule and topics for flex hours</span></span></div>", ""], "授業計画1": "<div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Reading&gt; Students practice reading skills and read and discuss a variety of contemporary texts in English. In addition, they will discuss extensive reading texts.</span></span></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Presentation&gt; Students will improve their ability to give a presentation in English confidently and comfortably over the course of three presentations. For each presentation, students will focus on several aspects of public speaking while refining the skills they have previously practiced.</span></span></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Seminar&gt; Students will develop the ability to discuss a topic with a group. The topics will challenge students to think beyond their experiences and cultural influences.</span></span></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Writing&gt; Students will complete essays that include introductions, outside sources, and conclusions. In addition, students will also complete tasks that improve fluency and understanding of the writing process.</span></span></span></div>", "授業外学習2": "<div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Reading&gt; Students read short texts and complete language development activities. They read graded readers for fluency and speed.</span></span></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Presentation&gt; Students will be required to work individually or as a group to prepare and practice their presentations and to do self-reflections after the presentations have been completed.</span></span></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Seminar&gt; Students will engage with test materials to prepare for class. Students learn vocabulary from the materials in order to ask discussion questions and use discussion skills. Students ﬁnd information on the Internet and evaluate it.</span></span></span></div><div><span style=\"font-size:13.28px;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\"><span dir=\"auto\" style=\"vertical-align:inherit;\">&lt;Writing&gt; Students complete writing activities, study model essays, and apply their understanding of the writing process by planning and drafting essays. They are also required to revise their essay assignments based on teacher feedback. They also complete homework tasks to practice skills and revise their essays.</span></span></span></div>"}, "評価": {"教科書/Required texts0": ["&lt;Presentation&gt;&lt;Seminar&gt;&lt;Writing&gt; Materials will be available on LUNA. You should bring your materials to class on your device (computer/tablet). Students will also be required to purchase an XReading card."], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students0": ["Conducted in class"], "学生による授業評価の方法Course Evaluation by Students1": ["Each class subject is arranged on the curriculum based on the Diploma Policy (DP) and Curriculum Policy (CP) established by each faculty and graduate school. By studying this course with DP/CP in mind, you will develop the abilities expected by each faculty and graduate school. The DP, CP, and curriculum table (list of classes, etc.) for each faculty/graduate school are posted in the link below, so please use them as a reference for your study plan. https://kwic.kwansei.ac.jp/cabinet/reference?typeCd=0&amp;cabinetId=557&amp;directLink=1 *Link to kwic (only current students can view)"], "成績評価Grading0": ["種別　Type備考　Note", "割合　Percentage", "評価基準等　Grading Criteria etc."], "成績評価Grading1": ["その他／Others (99)", "100 %", "See the Evaluation Note below"], "成績評価Grading2": ["備考　Note &lt;Presentation&gt; Students will be assessed on presentations made in class, the visual support, and written planning and reflection tasks.&lt;Reading&gt; Students will be assessed based on quizzes, unit discussions, extensive reading, and participation.&lt;Seminar&gt; Students are assessed on this course through unit discussion tests, test preparation materials, and article-related discussion preparation materials.&lt;Writing&gt; Students are assessed on the drafts of essays they write, quizzes, and in-class writing activities."], "更新日時/Date of Update0": ["2026年02月19日 18時08分16秒"], "項番No.0": [], "項番No.1": ["2026年度", "秋学期／Fall", "火曜２時限／Tuesday 2", "秋学期／Fall", "教室未定"], "項番No.2": ["2026年度", "秋学期／Fall", "水曜１時限／Wednesday 1", "秋学期／Fall", "教室未定"], "項番No.3": ["2026年度", "秋学期／Fall", "木曜２時限／Thursday 2", "秋学期／Fall", "教室未定"], "項番No.4": ["2026年度", "秋学期／Fall", "金曜３時限／Friday 3", "秋学期／Fall", "教室未定"]}, "campas": 1, "name": "【150】English Communication IV　Ａ／English Communication IV", "管理部署": 7, "単位数": 4, "担当者": "ジョーダン　Ｊ．（JORDAN JENNIFER ALINE） ", "履修基準年度": "１年", "履修登録方法": "予備登録", "開講期": 2, "時限1": 8, "時限2": 14, "時限3": 22, "時限4": 30, "評価1": 6, "成績評価備考": "備考　Note\n<Presentation> Students will be assessed on presentations made in class, the visual support, and written planning and reflection tasks.\n<Reading> Students will be assessed based on quizzes, unit discussions, extensive reading, and participation.\n<Seminar> Students are assessed on this course through unit discussion tests, test preparation materials, and article-related discussion preparation materials.\n<Writing> Students are assessed on the drafts of essays they write, quizzes, and in-class writing activities."}